prep. See Amidst.
prep. In the midst or middle of; surrounded or encompassed by;
   among.

v. be a regular or frequent visitor to a certain place
a. coming at short intervals or habitually
s. frequently encountered;

a. pleasing to the eye or mind especially through beauty or charm
s. having power to arouse interest
a. having the properties of a magnet; the ability to draw or pull;

n. Any one out of an indefinite number of persons; anyone;
   any person.
n. A person of consideration or standing.

r. on one occasion
r. as soon as
r. at a previous time;
